AUDIO_ENCODING_FLAC_VALUE - Static variable in enum com.google.cloud.dialogflow.v2beta1.AudioEncoding
[`FLAC`](https://xiph.org/flac/documentation.html) (Free Lossless Audio Codec) is the recommended encoding because it is lossless (therefore recognition is not compromised) and requires only about half the bandwidth of `LINEAR16`.
AUDIO_ENCODING_LINEAR_16_VALUE - Static variable in enum com.google.cloud.dialogflow.v2beta1.AudioEncoding

AUDIO_ENCODING_MULAW_VALUE - Static variable in enum com.google.cloud.dialogflow.v2beta1.AudioEncoding

AUDIO_ENCODING_OGG_OPUS_VALUE - Static variable in enum com.google.cloud.dialogflow.v2beta1.AudioEncoding
Opus encoded audio frames in Ogg container ([OggOpus](https://wiki.xiph.org/OggOpus)).
AUDIO_ENCODING_SPEEX_WITH_HEADER_BYTE_VALUE - Static variable in enum com.google.cloud.dialogflow.v2beta1.AudioEncoding
Although the use of lossy encodings is not recommended, if a very low bitrate encoding is required, `OGG_OPUS` is highly preferred over Speex encoding.
